title._content: Billie Samuels leaving to ride to Melbourne on a Malvern Star bicycle, 4 July 1934, by Sam Hood

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales
tag.author: 29454428@N08

description._content: "Miss Billie Samuels started on her attack on the women's record iiom Sydney to Melbourne, held by Miss Valsa Barbour, at 10 o'clock yesterday morning. She will ride to a schedule which will bring her to the Melbourne G.P.O. at 2 p.m. on Saturday, in total time of 3 days 7 hours. This is about three hours taster than the present record."
